ndrick Lamar, Soundgarden, Willie Nelson, and more. Catch all five nights of the iTunes Festival for free as a live or on-demand stream in the iTunes Store on your iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, Mac, or PC. Watch the performances on Apple TV or download the iTunes Festival app. And gear up for the shows by listening to the iTunes Festival at SXSW Artists station on iTunes Radio.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2014 13:12:17 PDT</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>CNN: Can Apple Help Make Hearing Aids Cool?</title>\r\n<link>http://www.cnn.com/2014/03/04/tech/innovation/apple-resound-hearing-aids/</link>\r\n<description>Apple and Danish company GN ReSound have teamed up to introduce a hearing aid thatâ€™s compatible with iPhone, iPad, and iPod touch, reports CNN.com. The LiNX hearing aid works with the accessibility options in iOS 7, letting users control it right from their Apple device. Doctors are hoping the high-tech factor will take some of the stigma out of seeking help for hearing loss. â€œThe association with Apple is going to make a great difference in getting people in the door in the first place,â€ audiologist Dr. Ken Smith says. </description>\r\n<pubDate>Fri, 07 Mar 2014 12:14:18 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>iPad Elevates Mountain Expeditions</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/your-verse/elevating-expedition/?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>In exploring some of the worldâ€™s tallest and most treacherous peaks, one new piece of equipment has become essential to mountaineers Adrian Ballinger and Emily Harrington: their iPad. Instead of relying on paper maps to prepare for their expeditions, they study details of remote regions using iPad and the Gaia GPS topography app. â€œFive years ago, it was hard to even get a paper map of some of these places,â€ Ballinger says. â€œNow with the iPad itâ€™s remarkable how much we can plan ahead.â€ The climbers also use iPad to blog and post photos during an expedition instead of recounting their story when the trek is over. And iPad is an important tool during extreme weather, as Ballinger and Harrington rely on it to make sure they stay on track. â€œIn a whiteout,â€ says Harrington, â€œbeing able to see where you are on the mountain can be a matter of life or death. iPad is the only way to tell where weâ€™re going.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 05 Mar 2014 11:49:54 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Appleâ€™s Oppenheimer to Retire at End of September</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2014/03/04Apples-Peter-Oppenheimer-to-Retire-at-the-End-of-September.html?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Apple today announced that Peter Oppenheimer, Appleâ€™s senior vice president and CFO, will retire at the end of September. Luca Maestri, Appleâ€™s vice president of Finance and corporate controller, will succeed Oppenheimer as CFO reporting to Apple CEO Tim Cook. Oppenheimer will transition the CFO role to Maestri in June and the balance of his responsibilities over the remaining time allowing for a seamless transition. â€œPeter has served as our CFO for the past decade as Appleâ€™s annual revenue grew from $8 billion to $171 billion and our global footprint expanded dramatically,â€ said Cook. â€œHis guidance, leadership and expertise have been instrumental to Appleâ€™s success, not only as our CFO but also in many areas beyond finance, as he frequently took on additional activities to assist across the company. His contributions and integrity as our CFO create a new benchmark for public company CFOs.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Tue, 04 Mar 2014 11:34:17 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Singapore School Finds New Ways to Educate With iPad</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/education/real-stories/nanyang/?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Educators at one of Singaporeâ€™s top public high schools have found that using iPad in the classroom is helping students excel and changing the way they interact with their lessons. In 2011, Nanyang Girlsâ€™ High School launched a program to introduce iPad in the curriculum. The initiative began with a single grade level, but has since expanded to include the entire student body. â€œThe interactive features definitely appeal to and engage the students more,â€ says history teacher Ong Lee Hua. Students are speaking up more in class and participating more in online discussions. And teachers also say iPad helps the girls learn to navigate the collaborative world theyâ€™ll be working in. â€œThe collaborative element of using iPad is pretty relevant in todayâ€™s world,â€ according to language arts teacher Cressandra Tan. â€œNot just relying on your own strengths, but the strengths of your group.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Tue, 04 Mar 2014 11:30:58 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Apple Rolls Out CarPlay for Safer iPhone Use on the Road</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2014/03/03Apple-Rolls-Out-CarPlay-Giving-Drivers-a-Smarter-Safer-More-Fun-Way-to-Use-iPhone-in-the-Car.html?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Apple has announced that leading auto manufacturers are rolling out CarPlay, the smarter and safer way to use iPhone in the car. CarPlay gives iPhone users an intuitive way to make calls, use Maps, listen to music, and access messages with a word or a touch. Users can control CarPlay from the carâ€™s native interface or push and hold the voice control button on the steering wheel to activate Siri. â€œCarPlay has been designed from the ground up to provide drivers with an incredible experience using their iPhone in the car,â€ said Greg Joswiak, Appleâ€™s vice president of iPhone and iOS Product Marketing. â€œiPhone users always want their content at their fingertips and CarPlay lets drivers use their iPhone in the car with minimized distraction.â€ Vehicles from Ferrari, Mercedes-Benz, and Volvo will premiere CarPlay to their drivers this week, while additional auto manufacturers will bring CarPlay to their drivers in the future.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Mon, 03 Mar 2014 11:18:58 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Laptop Mag Names Apple Best Notebook Brand Fifth Year in a Row</title>\r\n<link>http://blog.laptopmag.com/apple-brand-rating-2014 </link>\r\n<description>For the fifth consecutive year, Apple has been named overall winner in Laptop Magâ€™s â€œBest and Worst Laptop Brands.â€ The magazine evaluated notebooks from nine manufacturers in a range of categories, from reviews and tech support to design and software. â€œFor a remarkable fifth year in a row,â€ the magazine writes, â€œApple has proved once again that itâ€™s still the gold standard of laptop makers.â€ Apple won four out of eight categories and tied for first in two others, and all four MacBook models reviewed received Editorâ€™s Choice awards. â€œOften imitated, never duplicated,â€ the reviewers concluded. â€œThe clean, modern look of Appleâ€™s MacBook has set the standard for portability and power, which is why so many other notebooks look like clones.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2014 14:42:38 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Soundgarden to Perform at iTunes Festival SXSW</title>\r\n<link>http://sxsw.com/itunes-festival-sxsw</link>\r\n<description>Soundgarden will join an all-star lineup playing the iTunes Festival at SXSW on March 13, Apple has announced. The Seattle-based band will perform the entire â€œSuperunknownâ€ album to celebrate the recordingâ€™s 20th anniversary. The festival will be held March 11-15 in Austin, Texas, and will also feature Coldplay, Imagine Dragons, Pitbull, Keith Urban, and more. Youâ€™ll be able to watch the performances live or on demand from iTunes.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 26 Feb 2014 13:39:10 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>iTunes Festival Coming to SXSW</title>\r\n<link>http://www.itunes.com/festival</link>\r\n<description>The Apple iTunes Festival will make its U.S. debut March 11â€“15 at SXSW in Austin, Texas. The Festival features five nights of free concerts by amazing artists like Coldplay, Imagine Dragons, Pitbull, Keith Urban, Willie Nelson, ZEDD, and more. Performances are available to watch live or on-demand via iTunes on your iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, Apple TV, Mac, or PC. And songs from the concerts will be available for download only on iTunes. â€œThe iTunes Festival in London has become an incredible way for Apple to share its love of music with our customers,â€ said Eddy Cue, Apple senior vice president of Internet Software and Services. â€œWeâ€™re excited about the incredible lineup of artists performing and SXSW is the perfect place to debut the first iTunes Festival in the U.S.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2014 13:21:10 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>FileMaker Go for iPad and iPhone Apps Surpass 1 Million Downloads</title>\r\n<link>http://www.filemaker.com/r/applego1m</link>\r\n<description>FileMaker Inc. announced today that its FileMaker Go for iPad and iPhone apps have surpassed 1 million downloads from the iTunes App Store. FileMaker Go is a free app that allows users to remotely interact with FileMaker databases. â€œBusinesses are using the FileMaker Platform to create solutions that manage everything from sales contacts and inventory to medical data on iPad and iPhone,â€ FileMakerâ€™s Ryan Rosenberg said. â€œWith the recent launch of FileMaker 13, customers will find it easier than ever to design innovative mobile solutions.â€\r\n\r\n</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 05 Feb 2014 11:19:07 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>The Pen, Phone, and iPad: Obamaâ€™s Tech Push in U.S. Schools</title>\r\n<link>http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/04/us-usa-obama-education-idUSBREA130J520140204</link>\r\n<description>On a recent visit to a middle school in Maryland, President Obama â€œwielded an iPad to help make a point about how he hopes to do more for schools without more funding from Congress,â€ according to a Reuters report. Obama plans to modernize classrooms with technology, and Apple and other private companies have pledged to provide $750 million in tech products and services. Appleâ€™s commitment includes donating free iPads to disadvantaged schools. Obama said technology like this â€œmakes vivid and real math and science, in a way that is more interesting to the students.â€\r\n</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 05 Feb 2014 11:17:20 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>iPhone App Helps Fans Get More Yardage Out of Super Bowl Weekend </title>\r\n<link>http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/31/technology/For-Super-Bowl-Personalized-Phone-Alerts.html?_r=0</link>\r\n<description>Fans can use iPhone and iOS to personalize their Super Bowl weekend experience, reports The New York Timesâ€™ Nick Wingfield in an article about the NFLâ€™s iBeacon integration with the NFL Mobile app. At Times Square and MetLife Stadium, mobile technology can lead fans to the nearest stadium entrance, the closest place to buy merchandise, or where to view the Lombardi Trophy. Mobile announcements and alerts based on location are not new, but the article notes that experts say, â€œApple is further along with its version of the technology, which is why most alerts of this kind are now sent to iPhone users.â€ Manish Jha, the NFLâ€™s general manager of mobile, says, â€œThe power of this is it really is able to connect the real world, the brick-and-mortar world, with the virtual world with a level of granularity that hasnâ€™t existed before.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2014 11:53:10 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Apple Reports First-Quarter Results</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2014/01/23FY-14-First-Quarter-Results-Conference-Call.html?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Apple has announced financial results for its fiscal 2014 first quarter ended December 28, 2013. The company posted record quarterly revenue of $57.6 billion and quarterly net profit of $13.1 billion, or $14.50 per diluted share. The company sold 51 million iPhones, an all-time quarterly record, compared to 47.8 million in the year-ago quarter. Apple also sold 26 million iPads during the quarter, also an all-time quarterly record, compared to 22.9 million in the year-ago quarter. The company sold 4.8 million Macs, compared to 4.1 million in the year-ago quarter. â€œWe are really happy with our record iPhone and iPad sales, the strong performance of our Mac products and the continued growth of iTunes, software, and services,â€ said Tim Cook, Appleâ€™s CEO. â€œWe love having the most satisfied, loyal, and engaged customers, and are continuing to invest heavily in our future to make their experiences with our products and services even better.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2014 15:03:10 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Apple Expands Worldwide Access to Educational Content</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2014/01/21Apple-Expands-Worldwide-Access-to-Educational-Content.html?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Apple has announced that iBooks Textbooks and iTunes U Course Manager are expanding into new markets across Asia, Latin America, Europe, and elsewhere around the world. iBooks Textbooks bring Multi-Touch texts with dynamic, current, and interactive content to teachers and students in 51 countries. iTunes U Course Manager, available in 70 countries, allows educators to create and distribute courses for their own classrooms, or share them publicly, on the iTunes U app. â€œThe incredible content and tools available for iPad provide teachers with new ways to customize learning unlike ever before,â€ said Eddy Cue, Appleâ€™s senior vice president of Internet Software and Services. â€œWe canâ€™t wait to see how teachers in even more countries will create their new lesson plans with interactive textbooks, apps, and rich digital content.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2014 16:19:12 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Apple Devices Flow Into Corporate World</title>\r\n<link>http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304244904579278560822979176?mod=djkeywordÂ </link>\r\n<description>In The Wall Street Journal, tech reporter Daisuke Wakabayashi describes how Apple is expanding its reach into the business market. â€œThe iPhone has replaced the BlackBerry as the mobile phone of choice, as the iPad assumes tasks once reserved for PCs,â€ Wakabayashi writes. He notes that â€œApple is going mainstreamâ€ when it comes to the corporate world, and he profiles multiple large enterprises â€” including SAP, Nordstrom, and Cisco â€” that have rolled out iOS and other Apple devices to their employees. In fact, according to Good Technology, â€œMore than 90 percent of all business apps were deployed on Appleâ€™s iOS mobile-operating system in the third quarter.â€</description>\r\n<pubDate>Fri, 10 Jan 2014 12:31:56 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>Yahoo Tech Reviews the New Mac Pro</title>\r\n<link>http://www.yahoo.com/tech/the-new-mac-pro-sleek-powerful-and-sooo-apple-72506916039.html</link>\r\n<description>Yahoo Techâ€™s David Pogue looks at the all-new Mac Pro, calling it an â€œinsanely powerfulâ€ computer designed for professional creative and scientific users. Heâ€™s impressed with its horsepower, noting that â€œevery wire, every circuit, every chip has been designed for speed,â€ and he says the desktopâ€™s â€œace in the hole is two top-of-the-line graphics cards.â€ Pogue points out that the Mac Pro handles pro apps like Final Cut Pro X, Photoshop, and Mathematica â€œfaster than any Mac ever tested,â€ saving professionals time and money. â€œThe Mac Pro, in every possible way, is a bet on the future,â€ writes Pogue.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Wed, 08 Jan 2014 11:14:15 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>App Store Sales Top $10 Billion in 2013</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/pr/library/2014/01/07App-Store-Sales-Top-10-Billion-in-2013.html?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Apple announced that customers spent over $10 billion on the App Store in 2013, including over $1 billion in December alone. App Store customers downloaded almost three billion apps in December, making it the most successful month in App Store history. â€œWeâ€™d like to thank our customers for making 2013 the best year ever for the App Store,â€ said Eddy Cue, Appleâ€™s senior vice president of Internet Software and Services. â€œThe lineup of apps for the holiday season was astonishing and we look forward to seeing what developers create in 2014.â€ Appleâ€™s developers have now earned $15 billion on the App Store. </description>\r\n<pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2014 11:25:35 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>iPad Can Be Another Pair of Eyes in Operating Room</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/ipad/life-on-ipad/new-eyes-for-hands-on-surgery/?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>Liver surgery is a very complex operation, requiring extensive planning and research before a doctor ever enters the operating room. To help improve the process and minimize the risks of this delicate operation, doctors in Japan teamed up with a German research institute to develop an iPad app for use during liver surgeries. The app shows three-dimensional surgical data, helps pinpoint the exact location of blood vessels, and assesses potential risks in real time. â€œThe visualization of liver blood vessels puts surgeons at ease, and it helps to ensure that the right incisions are made at the right time,â€ says Dr. Itaru Endo of Yokohama City University. The number of doctors using iPad apps during surgery is growing â€” the apps not only help save lives, they save money. â€œAugmented reality and other features of the app can replace equipment that costs half a million dollars,â€ Endo says.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Thu, 02 Jan 2014 14:42:56 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n<title>iPad Transforms Napa Wineryâ€™s Production Process</title>\r\n<link>http://www.apple.com/ipad/life-on-ipad/the-modern-making-of-a-vintage/?sr=hotnews.rss</link>\r\n<description>At Palmaz Vineyards in Napa, California, iPad has improved the way the facility operates, from its vineyard to its tanks. Winemaker Christian GastÃ³n Palmaz uses iPad to manage the vineyard and gather data that helps him make informed vine-tending decisions. iPad also has replaced complex industrial controls inside the winery. Palmaz uses an enterprise-level app that automates the labor-intensive, conventional fermentation process. â€œiPad removes the burden of data collecting and frees up our brilliant winemakers to focus on the art of winemaking,â€ says Palmaz.</description>\r\n<pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2013 11:30:19 PST</pubDate>\r\n</item>\r\n</channel>\r\n</rss>', 1395671280);
