('http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_sport.rss', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\r\n<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" media="screen" href="/~d/styles/rss2full.xsl"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" media="screen" href="http://rss.cnn.com/~d/styles/itemcontent.css"?><rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:feedburner="http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0" version="2.0">\r\n<channel>\r\n<title>CNN.com - Sport</title>\r\n<link>http://edition.cnn.com/SPORT/index.html?eref=rss_sport</link>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n<language>en-US</language>\r\n<copyright>Copyright 2014 Cable News Network LP, LLLP.</copyright>\r\n<pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2014 08:52:41 EDT</pubDate>\r\n<ttl>10</ttl>\r\n<image>\r\n<title>CNN.com - Sport</title>\r\n<link>http://edition.cnn.com/SPORT/index.html?eref=rss_sport</link>\r\n<url>http://i.cdn.turner.com/cnn/.e/img/1.0/logo/cnn.logo.rss.gif</url>\r\n<width>144</width>\r\n<height>33</height>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n</image>\r\n<atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_sport" /><feedburner:info uri="rss/edition_sport" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><item><title>F1 tech to benefit road cars?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/motorsport/jody-scheckter-formula-one-2014/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/CldoZmcaRcA/index.html</link><description>The big winners of this Formula One season could be road drivers rather than F1 racers, according to one former world champion.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/CldoZmcaRcA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2014 12:23:30 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/motorsport/jody-scheckter-formula-one-2014/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Ferrari catching up''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/motorsport/ferrari-fernando-alonso-ricciardo-f1/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/-Zj8imVagA8/index.html</link><description>The 2014 Formula One season may have only just got going, but Ferrari is already playing catch-up. That''s the view of technical director James Allison, who admits the team is some way behind early pacesetters Mercedes.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/-Zj8imVagA8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 22 Mar 2014 16:01:11 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/motorsport/ferrari-fernando-alonso-ricciardo-f1/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>F1''s weird trip into the unknown</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/13/sport/motorsport/formula-one-2014-motorsport/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/OQF895GNX3s/index.html</link><description>Mercedes driver Lewis Hamilton sums up the dawn of a new Formula One era in three juicy words -- weird, mind-blowing and challenging.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/OQF895GNX3s" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Mar 2014 15:16:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/13/sport/motorsport/formula-one-2014-motorsport/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Murray splits with Lendl</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/tennis/murray-lendl-tennis-split/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/rbAOL56TS7U/index.html</link><description>With Ivan Lendl by his side, Andy Murray opened his grand slam account, won Olympic gold and finally ended Britain''s wait for a men''s singles champion at Wimbledon. But the two have now gone their separate ways.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/rbAOL56TS7U" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 22 Mar 2014 17:47:59 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/tennis/murray-lendl-tennis-split/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Djokovic denies Federer in final</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/16/sport/tennis/tennis-roger-federer-novak-djokovic/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/WdPk7dYLCCI/index.html</link><description>Novak Djokovic comes from behind to defeat Roger Federer in three sets at the Indian Wells Masters event Sunday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/WdPk7dYLCCI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Mar 2014 10:02:13 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/16/sport/tennis/tennis-roger-federer-novak-djokovic/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Li shrugs off shock loss</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/15/sport/tennis/li-na-indian-wells-tennis/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/X-WvKK48tI8/index.html</link><description>For Li Na, it was no big deal. For Flavia Pennetta, it was one of the most important victories of her tennis career.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/X-WvKK48tI8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2014 09:12:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/15/sport/tennis/li-na-indian-wells-tennis/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Woods in doubt for Masters</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/18/sport/golf/golf-tiger-woods/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/TDuYptHLUw0/index.html</link><description>Tiger Woods is in danger of being forced to miss the opportunity of recording a fifth Augusta triumph after being forced to withdraw from this week''s Arnold Palmer Invitational with a back injury.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/TDuYptHLUw0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 22 Mar 2014 13:49:29 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/18/sport/golf/golf-tiger-woods/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Idiot'' John Daly seeks help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/golf/john-daly-pga-tour-golf/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/o8FMn0CySCM/index.html</link><description>It''s not the first time John Daly has had to ask for help -- but it must be one of the most embarrassing.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/o8FMn0CySCM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2014 12:45:34 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/golf/john-daly-pga-tour-golf/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>James Bond''s favorite bunker</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/11/sport/golf/knightsbridge-connery-bond-golf/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/K4T4OpP4hv8/index.html</link><description>Below ground in central London is a bunker every self-respecting golfer is desperate to find -- even international man of mystery James Bond.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/K4T4OpP4hv8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 11 Mar 2014 09:40:30 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/11/sport/golf/knightsbridge-connery-bond-golf/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Crazy'' day for World Cup champ</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/15/sport/marcel-hirscher-world-cup-skiing/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/a587rgjdbhY/index.html</link><description>Marcel Hirscher may have come away from Sochi without a Winter Olympics gold medal, but the Austrian has confirmed his reputation as the most consistent men''s skier on the World Cup circuit.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/a587rgjdbhY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2014 09:07:25 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/15/sport/marcel-hirscher-world-cup-skiing/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ligety, Shiffrin golden glow</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/08/sport/skiing-ligety-shiffrin/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/OqLX62Mx1R0/index.html</link><description>Ted Ligety and Mikaela Shiffrin continue to bask in the golden glow of Olympic triumph as the American pair record impressive World Cup victories Saturday in their specialist disciplines.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/OqLX62Mx1R0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2014 19:35:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/08/sport/skiing-ligety-shiffrin/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ghostly lights ... and uphill torture?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/20/sport/streif-vertical-up-kitzbuhel-skiing/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/tMc2nZKHSgI/index.html</link><description>The ghostly lights wind up from the base of the mountain. Heart rates are also rising. Held in subzero conditions, this night race takes place on one of the world''s most notoriously treacherous downhill skiing courses -- but these hardy souls are tackling it in the opposite direction.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/tMc2nZKHSgI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 20 Feb 2014 09:04:28 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/20/sport/streif-vertical-up-kitzbuhel-skiing/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Venus rises from under covers</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/tennis/venus-williams-sjogrens-syndrome/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/diHMkxu9oac/index.html</link><description>Everyone has had one of those mornings -- you wake up groggy, can''t face going to work, dive back under the covers and go back to sleep. Tennis star Venus Williams knows exactly how that feels -- but she is beating the autoimmune disease that derailed her career.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/diHMkxu9oac" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2014 10:49:58 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/tennis/venus-williams-sjogrens-syndrome/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Jockey''s new life through a lens</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/richard-dunwoody-horse-racing-photography/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/k-IWBuwUgcU/index.html</link><description>Former champion jockey Richard Dunwoody has gone from riding winners to highlighting the plight of working animals in his second career as a photographer.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/k-IWBuwUgcU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2014 08:08:58 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/richard-dunwoody-horse-racing-photography/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Tattoos, broken bones and trophies</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/tai-woffinden-speedway-tattoos/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/yBPR8kUR_rk/index.html</link><description>"Pain is weakness leaving the body." Tai Woffinden''s arms, hands, face, neck and shoulders are all adorned with tattoos. But most revealing is the design on his back -- a portrait of his father and racing mentor, and one of the letters he wrote to his son before passing away in 2010.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/yBPR8kUR_rk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Mar 2014 10:00:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/tai-woffinden-speedway-tattoos/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Relief for Moyes and Man Utd</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/football/manchester-united-olympiakos-champions-league/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/h7U1hs93kEk/index.html</link><description>Manchester United was left reeling Sunday after a loss to Liverpool but there was respite for under-fire manager David Moyes and his team Wednesday as they rallied to advance in the Champions League.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/h7U1hs93kEk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Mar 2014 09:06:30 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/19/sport/football/manchester-united-olympiakos-champions-league/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Serena Williams'' best move?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/03/18/spc-open-court-serena-williams-preview.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/i_J8-XZJHVs/spc-open-court-serena-williams-preview.cnn.html</link><description>The world No. 1 shows off her incredible volley. CNN''s Pat Cash reports.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/i_J8-XZJ