k="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/28/unguarded-jason-collins-returns.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/AVo0mIa-1t8/unguarded-jason-collins-returns.cnn.html</link><description>Rachel Nichols exclusive sitdown interview with Jason Collins, the NBA''s first openly gay basketball player.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/AVo0mIa-1t8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 03 Mar 2014 06:06:16 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/28/unguarded-jason-collins-returns.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bode Miller reflects on Sochi</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2014/02/19/bode-miller-intvw-nichols.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/oY6bJjixUeA/bode-miller-intvw-nichols.cnn.html</link><description>Six-time Olympic medalist Bode Miller sits down with Rachel Nichols.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/oY6bJjixUeA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2014 07:53:09 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2014/02/19/bode-miller-intvw-nichols.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Photos: 2014 Winter Paralympics</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/08/world/gallery/paralympics-2014/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/2NQjMUZgzjE/index.html</link><description>Photos: 2014 Winter Paralympic games&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/2NQjMUZgzjE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2014 09:16:21 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/08/world/gallery/paralympics-2014/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Here''s Sochi''s real winner</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/sochi-winter-olympics-medals-per-capita/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/aNQ3FtDZT3E/index.html</link><description>Russian President Vladimir Putin is no doubt leaving Sochi with a smile on his face: True, his beloved men''s hockey team crashed out of Winter Olympics competition before medals were up for grabs, but the host nation claimed 33 medals overall, the most of any country at the Games.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/aNQ3FtDZT3E" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Feb 2014 11:05:07 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/sochi-winter-olympics-medals-per-capita/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Sochi: The coolest gear on show</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/sochi-olympics-cool-gear/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/6mfQrjCA5oQ/index.html</link><description>The Winter Olympics'' motto was " Hot. Cool. Yours." From eye-popping helmet designs to Formula One-influenced bobsleigh, the Sochi 2014 Games offered a bewildering array of technological innovation as well as some seriously "pimped up" athlete equipment.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/6mfQrjCA5oQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Feb 2014 11:01:30 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/sochi-olympics-cool-gear/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Hoop star turns master chef</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/sport/human-to-hero-darryl-middleton/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/d4oIWd_8_Nc/index.html</link><description>He was an outstanding talent who never made it in the NBA, before he established himself as one of the most famous American players in European basketball history.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/d4oIWd_8_Nc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 12 Mar 2014 11:44:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/sport/human-to-hero-darryl-middleton/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bond villain who lived another day</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/05/sport/sebastien-foucan-free-running-bond/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/qd3SRQQEbaA/index.html</link><description>There are not many Bond villains who survive to tell the tale of their encounter with 007. But pioneering free runner Sebastien Foucan has proved even more elusive than his incredibly agile bomb-maker who was eventually blown away by Daniel Craig in "Casino Royale."&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/qd3SRQQEbaA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 05 Mar 2014 07:57:59 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/05/sport/sebastien-foucan-free-running-bond/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Imagine trying to ski blind</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/26/sport/gallagher-evans-winter-paralympics-sochi/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~3/ZvJ5YOF4qxw/index.html</link><description>Imagine hurtling down a mountain at 60 miles an hour. Now imagine doing it virtually blind. For Kelly Gallagher, it''s a thrilling reality. She might not quite reach the speeds of fully-sighted skiers -- Olympic champions can clock upwards of 90 mph -- but it is nonetheless a daunting prospect.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_sport/~4/ZvJ5YOF4qxw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 26 Feb 2014 09:17:49 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/26/sport/gallagher-evans-winter-paralympics-sochi/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>