mg src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/jXS2_8m7FEA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2014 06:14:24 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/football/zaatari-refugee-camp/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Fan crosses world, game canceled </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/13/sport/football/football-everton-malaysia-fan/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/t025FVbeNes/index.html</link><description>It started as a dream trip from Malaysia to watch his beloved Everton play for the first time only, for the game to be called off due to the bad weather sweeping Britain.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/t025FVbeNes" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Feb 2014 08:45:23 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/13/sport/football/football-everton-malaysia-fan/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Blatter readies for re-election</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/07/sport/football/football-sepp-blatter-fifa-election/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Gyw3QDsHKZQ/index.html</link><description>World governing body FIFA has had just two presidents in 40 years and current incumbent Sepp Blatter has given his strongest indication yet that he wants to extend that record further.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Gyw3QDsHKZQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Feb 2014 14:20:48 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/07/sport/football/football-sepp-blatter-fifa-election/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Donovan, Henry on cup contenders</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/18/ws-world-cup-predictions-henry-donovan.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/9uz8_2z1CIE/ws-world-cup-predictions-henry-donovan.cnn.html</link><description>Thierry Henry and Landon Donovan weigh in on World Cup hopefuls.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/9uz8_2z1CIE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 09:49:13 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/18/ws-world-cup-predictions-henry-donovan.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Draw gives chance for revenge</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/12/06/sport/football/world-cup-draw-brazil-2014/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/zvuhOGG9QkY/index.html</link><description>Spain will face the Netherlands in a rematch of the 2010 World Cup final, as the draw for Brazil next year brings up some intriguing clashes.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/zvuhOGG9QkY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jan 2014 05:55:02 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/12/06/sport/football/world-cup-draw-brazil-2014/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Messi breaks Barcelona record </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/16/sport/football/barcelona-milan-messi/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/jlxnP1g5G9c/index.html</link><description>Lionel Messi became Barcelona''s all-time leading goalscorer after hitting a hat-trick in his side''s 7-0 win over Osasuna Sunday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/jlxnP1g5G9c" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2014 14:25:34 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/16/sport/football/barcelona-milan-messi/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Can Liverpool end 20 years of pain?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/football/liverpool-v-manchester-united-sturridge-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Ekptfu5YXiQ/index.html</link><description>A familiar refrain for many football fans is that it''s "the hope that kills you."&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Ekptfu5YXiQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2014 08:58:06 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/football/liverpool-v-manchester-united-sturridge-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Zidane and Ronaldo tackle poverty</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/03/07/football-match-for-poverty.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/WSUcAaxjuM0/football-match-for-poverty.cnn.html</link><description>Football icons, Ronaldo, Zinedine Zidane and Luis Figo return for the UN''s Match Against Poverty.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/WSUcAaxjuM0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 11:13:21 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/03/07/football-match-for-poverty.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bayern chief accepts jail term</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/hoeness-bayern-resignation/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/O_JjoUCpcpI/index.html</link><description>The president of one of the world''s most famous football clubs has decided not to appeal a jail sentence for tax evasion as he stepped down from key roles at the reigning German and European champions Bayern Munich.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/O_JjoUCpcpI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 09:47:13 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/14/sport/hoeness-bayern-resignation/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Barca and PSG into last eight</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/sport/football/champions-league-barcelona-manchester-city/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/cfC6kYeG4LY/index.html</link><description>Barcelona made it through to the quarterfinals of the Champions League for the seventh year in succession after defeating Manchester City while PSG overcame Bayer Leverkusen to book its place in the next round&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/cfC6kYeG4LY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 15 Mar 2014 19:22:13 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/sport/football/champions-league-barcelona-manchester-city/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Healing scars for war children</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/world/africa/football-scars-liberia-war/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/i8QJ_npLoUM/index.html</link><description>A football training scheme is helping children growing up in the aftermath of Liberia''s civil war.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/i8QJ_npLoUM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 15 Mar 2014 17:38:29 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/12/world/africa/football-scars-liberia-war/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Does soccer need a sin-bin?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/10/sport/football/champions-league-last-16-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Yjcj049ZJbU/index.html</link><description>Europe''s top football clubs will resume their battles for a place in the quarterfinals of the continent''s biggest competition this month, with some still reeling after tie-changing moments of controversy. Last month''s last-16 opening legs provided bitter lessons for two English teams hoping to make their mark against benchmark opponents, and prompted calls for changes to the game''s rules.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Yjcj049ZJbU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2014 15:28:23 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/10/sport/football/champions-league-last-16-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Platini puts faith in referees</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/10/sport/football/michel-platini-uefa-euro-2016-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/9Fvr4ZFxR7Q/index.html</link><description>UEFA president Michel Platini remains resistant to the introduction of goal-line technology for Europe''s top competitions.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/9Fvr4ZFxR7Q" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2014 15:27:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/10/sport/football/michel-platini-uefa-euro-2016-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ronaldo puts Real top of La Liga</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/09/sport/football/real-madrid-juventus-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/3leqpaf2ip8/index.html</link><description>Real Madrid return to the top of La Liga after a routine 3-0 win over Levante in the Bernabeu Sunday with Cristiano Ronaldo scoring the opener.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/3leqpaf2ip8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 09 Mar 2014 16:52:39 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/09/sport/football/real-madrid-juventus-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Platini backs Russia for World Cup</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/06/sport/platini-paralympic-boycott-ukraine/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/6TTeqsIX_34/index.html</link><description>The political issue of whether Russia should play at the 2014 World Cup is a familiar one for UEFA president Michel Platini, who had his own decision to make as a player representing France at Argentina ''78.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/6TTeqsIX_34" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 07 Mar 2014 09:02:00 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/06/sport/platini-paralympic-boycott-ukraine/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ukraine claims USA scalp</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/05/sport/kosovo-ukraine-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/a5iLbN17eXE/index.html</link><description>It may not be the most significant result in the history of the Ukraine national team but the smattering of supporters who were present in Larnaca, Cyprus, won''t forget this victory in a hurry.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/a5iLbN17eXE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 11 Mar 2014 04:22:03 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/05/sport/kosovo-ukraine-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Puyol to leave Barca</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/04/sport/football/barcelona-captain-carles-puyol-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Q0O1LyfkCeo/index.html</link><description>Is it the end of an era for a side recognized as one of the best in football history? Four players made the squads for all three of Barcelona''s Champions League titles -- and now the first, club captain Carles Puyol, is set to leave.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Q0O1LyfkCeo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2014 13:00:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/04/sport/football/barcelona-captain-carles-puyol-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What did Michael Owen do next?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/04/sport/football/michael-owen-horse-racing-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Ik0cMBMTbmg/index.html</link><description>How do you replace the adrenaline-filled emotion of scoring one of the greatest goals in World Cup history when your football career ends?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Ik0cMBMTbmg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2014 08:32:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/04/sport/football/michael-owen-horse-racing-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Best in the business?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/25/davies-bayern-munich-business-rummenigge.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/JpCQHNPIXB8/davies-bayern-munich-business-rummenigge.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Amanda Davies asks CEO Karl-Heinz Rummenigge how Bayern Munich continues to be successful.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/JpCQHNPIXB8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 25 Feb 2014 11:53:49 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/02/25/davies-bayern-munich-business-rummenigge.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Man City win League Cup</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/02/sport/football/football-manchester-city-pellegrini/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/bZ8Cksbe0E0/index.html</link><description>Samir Nasri scores the decisive second goal as Manchester City comes from behind to beat Sunderland 3-1 in the English League Cup final at Wembley.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/bZ8Cksbe0E0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 09 Mar 2014 15:07:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/02/sport/football/football-manchester-city-pellegrini/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>EPL boss fined $168K for headbutt </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/01/sport/football/football-pardew-headbutt-fine/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/DA9cXl-Ldak/index.html</link><description>Newcastle United fine manager Alan Pardew Â£100,000 ($168,000) for head-butting an opposition player during an English Premier League match.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/DA9cXl-Ldak" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 09 Mar 2014 15:08:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/01/sport/football/football-pardew-headbutt-fine/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Secrets of the world''s best club</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/25/sport/bayern-munich-rummenigge-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/phQVWqqLIYA/index.html</link><description>Bayern Munich might be enjoying one of the most successful periods in its history, but chairman Karl-Heinz Rummenigge tells CNN that it might have been very different if not for one key decision.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/phQVWqqLIYA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 26 Feb 2014 13:08:15 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/25/sport/bayern-munich-rummenigge-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Barca pays ''voluntary'' $18.5M tax</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/football/football-barcelona-tax-payment-neymar-deal/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/2nbF2B7uVxo/index.html</link><description>Barcelona pays $18.5 million in additional taxes on Monday, while denying any fiscal "irregularities" in its purchase of Brazilian superstar Neymar, which is now under investigation by a court.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/2nbF2B7uVxo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 04 Mar 2014 07:08:23 EST</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/02/24/sport/football/football-barcelona-tax-payment-neymar-deal/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>England failing to tackle football racism?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/24/sport/football/racism-in-football-kick-it-out-garth-crooks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/kO8tN5GYXqM/index.html</link><description>England prides itself on being the home of football, but is the nation dysfunctional in dealing with racist abuse?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/kO8tN5GYXqM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2014 08:47:08 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/24/sport/football/racism-in-football-kick-it-out-garth-crooks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Messi inspires Barcelona in El Clasico </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/23/sport/football/real-madrid-barcelona-clasico/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/T6rDGjuq-C8/index.html</link><description>Lionel Messi scored a hat-trick in Barcelona''s 4-3 win over Real Madrid on Sunday that had just about everything. Atletico Madrid, not one of the two Spanish giants, now leads the standings.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/T6rDGjuq-C8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2014 19:27:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/23/sport/football/real-madrid-barcelona-clasico/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Still in the Champions League hunt </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/23/sport/football/tottenham-southampton-premier-league/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/S7zId2wTcXM/index.html</link><description>Arsenal lost 6-0 to Chelsea in English football''s Premier League and it looked like another side from North London would suffer a heavy defeat Sunday when Tottenham fell behind 2-0 to Southampton. But unlike Arsenal, Tottenham rallied and pulled to within six points of its fourth-place rival.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/S7zId2wTcXM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2014 12:38:32 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/23/sport/football/tottenham-southampton-premier-league/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bayern Munich on the brink </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/22/sport/football/football-bayern-close-in-on-title-in-record-time/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/wi8xQ-Gfk-o/index.html</link><description>Pep Guardiola''s side may have left it late to beat Mainz but will wrap up the Bundesliga title in super quick time next Tuesday should they defeat Hertha Berlin.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/wi8xQ-Gfk-o" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 22 Mar 2014 17:50:29 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/22/sport/football/football-bayern-close-in-on-title-in-record-time/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Platini backs referees</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/03/10/intv-platini-uefa-goal-line-tech.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/pabMxuAeTjo/intv-platini-uefa-goal-line-tech.cnn.html</link><description>UEFA president Michel Platini tells CNN''s Amanda Davies why he does not want goal-line technology.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/pabMxuAeTjo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 11:16:13 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2014/03/10/intv-platini-uefa-goal-line-tech.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Chelsea ruin Wenger''s big day</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/22/sport/football/football-chelsea-arsenal-wenger-1000-defeat/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/wq9FtZDUJDQ/index.html</link><description>Arsenal fans were hoping for a fairytale win against old rivals Chelsea to mark Arsene Wenger''s 1,000th game in charge. Instead, they endured a nightmare.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/wq9FtZDUJDQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 22 Mar 2014 13:55:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/22/sport/football/football-chelsea-arsenal-wenger-1000-defeat/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bayern to face Manchester United</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/21/sport/football/champions-league-quarterfinal-draw/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/-Pj1xTKD8is/index.html</link><description>Defending champion Bayern Munich will play Manchester United in the quarterfinals of the European Champions League.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/-Pj1xTKD8is" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2014 19:28:37 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/21/sport/football/champions-league-quarterfinal-draw/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Reformer calls for 2022 vote rerun</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/football/qatar-2022-world-cup-vote-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/1_F7Qrk8vZQ/index.html</link><description>Leading former FIFA insider Alexandra Wrage is calling for a new vote over the selection of the 2022 World Cup hosts given the ongoing controversy surrounding the decision to award Qatar the event.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/1_F7Qrk8vZQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2014 07:36:03 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/20/sport/football/qatar-2022-world-cup-vote-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Unhappy homecoming for Drogba</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/18/sport/football/football-chelsea-galatasaray-real-madrid/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~3/Mh0BBx6tAl4/index.html</link><description>Didier Drogba returned to a hero''s welcome at Chelsea but the Galatasaray striker was shown little mercy as the Turkish club was sent crashing out of the Champions League.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_football/~4/Mh0BBx6tAl4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2014 17:47:18 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/18/sport/football/football-chelsea-galatasaray-real-madrid/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>God in a city of football faith?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/18/sport/football/daniel-sturridge-england-liverpool-football/index.html</guid><link>